3.  PERMITTED USES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The Recipient MAY:

(a) Reproduce experimental results described in arXiv:2606.09570 using
    the evaluation pipeline provided;

(b) Evaluate language models on the benchmark in a non-commercial,
    academic research context;

(c) Modify the evaluation code solely to adapt it to the Recipient's
    non-commercial research computing environment, provided that any such
    modifications are not distributed to third parties;

(d) Cite and reference the Work in academic publications, theses, or
    conference presentations, provided proper attribution is given
    (see Section 5);

(e) Share evaluation results and derived metrics (e.g., accuracy scores)
    in academic publications, provided the raw data and dataset files
    are NOT included or redistributed.

