━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The Recipient SHALL NOT, without prior written consent from the Licensor:

DISTRIBUTION & REDISTRIBUTION
(a) Redistribute, share, publish, upload, mirror, or otherwise make the
    Work or any portion thereof available to any third party, in any form
    or medium, including but not limited to file-sharing platforms, cloud
    storage, academic repositories, or open-source hosting services;

(b) Include the Work, or any portion of the dataset files or data samples,
    in any publicly accessible repository or system;

DERIVATIVE WORKS
(c) Create, publish, or distribute any Derivative Work based on the Work,
    for any purpose, including academic, non-commercial, or open-source
    purposes, without prior written permission from the Licensor;

(d) Use the Work as a foundation, seed, or component to build a new
    benchmark, dataset, evaluation framework, or leaderboard;

(e) Translate, reformat, augment, or otherwise transform the data into
    another dataset or resource for distribution;

COMMERCIAL USE
(f) Use the Work, in whole or in part, for any Commercial Purpose;

(g) Use the Work to train, fine-tune, distill, or otherwise improve any
    AI model or system intended for commercial deployment;

(h) Integrate the Work into any product, service, or platform offered
    to third parties for compensation;

PRIVACY & SECURITY
(i) Attempt to re-identify, de-anonymize, or infer the identity of any
    individual whose interaction data may have contributed to the Work;

(j) Use the Work to extract, reconstruct, or infer private user
    information, conversation content, or behavioral patterns beyond
    what is necessary for the permitted Research Purpose;

(k) Use the Work for surveillance, profiling, psychological manipulation,
    targeted advertising, or any purpose that may cause harm to
    individuals or groups;

INTEGRITY
(l) Remove, alter, or obscure any copyright notice, attribution
    statement, or license terms accompanying the Work;

(m) Misrepresent the origin of the Work, including claiming authorship
    or falsely attributing the Work to a different source;

(n) Transfer, assign, or sublicense any rights granted under this
    License to any third party.

